[As you will see from the previous postings referenced below, _Y. pestis_
is most usually recovered from ground rodents and cats. With the fall
hunting season upon us, it is hopefully not too late to remind hunters not
to shoot non-alert game; such animals may well be ill, if not from plague,
then from a wide variety of other equally unpleasant conditions, all
capable of qualifying the hunter for a Darwin Award. - Mod.MHJ]
